text:
You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK." 

You know what to do.

You pack a small suitcase, and arrange a flight to West Palm Beach. You arrive in West Palm, and are met by a man in a black suit. He takes you to limo and you are driven across the Intracoastal Waterway. You are taken to a large house on a small island.

"Welcome to Mar-a-Lago," reads a large sign.

You are taken to a room with a large desk. On the desk is an icy glass full of a cola drink of some kind.

You sit down, and reach for a small object in your briefcase. A men with orange skin and an unfortunate hairdo enters and sits behind the desk.

"Mr. President," he says, "I am Donald Trump.

"No sh**," says Obama.

"I know," says Trump, "I'm just trying to build up the drama."

"Oh, so it's drama you want?" says Obama, as he levels a matte gray pistol at the man behind the desk.

"No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no" says the man behind the desk, pursing his lips and raising clenched hands in front of his face.

There is a momentary spitting sound, and red flowers appear beneath unnaturally blond hair.

"I'm not a fan of drama," says Obama, as he holsters the pistol and takes a sip of the drink.

Two man silently enter the room, and pull the man behind the desk out by his tiny oxfords.

Obama moves to the seat behind the desk.

"So," he says, "What's the job?"
